        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 29 at 1:54PM EDT by NWS Caribou ME</headline>
        <description>At 154 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Sherman to near Haynesville to 7 miles
northeast of Reed Plantation. Movement was northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 45 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Houlton, Hodgdon, Sherman, Island Falls, Smyrna, Amity, Haynesville,
Cary Plantation, Reed Plantation, Littleton, Linneus, Monticello,
Oakfield, New Limerick, Ludlow, Weston, Cary, Dyer Brook, Reed, and
Orient.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 95 between mile markers 289 and 304.
US Highway 1 between Orient and Monticello.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with these storms.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
